svt_axi_system_transaction Class Reference

Inheritance diagram for class svt_axi_system_transaction:

List of all members.

Detailed Description

This class encapsulates system level information pertaining to a transaction. System level information includes a master transaction and associated snoop and slave transactions.

  function void
 svt_axi_system_transaction::set_snoop_type_for_coherent_transaction
 (  svt_axi_snoop_transaction :: snoop_xact_type_enum dynamic_snoop_type  ) 

This function associates the snoop transaction with coherent transaction dynamically at the run time The user can set the snoop type at the run time by making use of pre_coherent_and_snoop_transaction_association callback By default the value of is_dynamic_snoop_type_set is 0 , so to enable dynamic mapping this function sets this value to 1

dynamic_snoop_type - The snoop transaction type corresponding to the master transaction

 svt_axi_snoop_transaction  attribute
 svt_axi_system_transaction::associated_snoop_xacts[$]

When the axi_interface_type is AXI_ACE, master_xact represents a coherent transaction received from the master. In this case, if snoop transactions were sent to other masters corresponding to this coherent transaction, associated_snoop_xacts [$] stores the associated snoop transactions.

 svt_axi_system_transaction::expected_snoop_addr[$]

If axi_interface_type is AXI_ACE, this variable represents the snoop addresses expected to be sent on each port for master_xact Currently used only for READONCE and WRITEUNIQUE transaction because these can span across multiple cache lines

 int  attribute
 svt_axi_system_transaction::slave_port_id[$]

port_id of the slave transaction(s) corresponding to the master transaction. By default this is empty, indicating that no slave transaction has been associated yet. Once any one slave transaction has been associated to a master transaction, this value gets updated to the port_id of that slave transaction.
